docs.text: set in a mythical kingdom , the film follows the adventures of kuzco ( david spade ) , an arrogant and egocentric emperor .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when kuzco fires his power-hungry advisor , yzma ( eartha kitt ) , she and her " assistant " kronk ( seinfeld's patrick warburton ) change him into a llama .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: kuzco then gets stranded in the jungle and must rely on pacha ( john goodman ) , a llama-herder whose home was to be replaced by kuzco's water world theme park , to save him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: then the fun starts .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: for the next sixty minutes , the audience is treated to something unheard of in disney films these days : imagination .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: yzma , voiced by the talented singer eartha kitt , looks like a cross between norma desmond , joan crawford , and a really old vegas showgirl .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the dialogue between her and her oblivious assistant kronk is quick , sharp , and feels like an episode of seinfeld ( which would make sense ) .

docs.text: david spade and john goodman's character interactions make you feel like you're watching an old hope/crosby film .
